&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Himachal Pradesh.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Himachal Pradesh became the 5th fully literate State/UT in India, as announced during the International Literacy Day (ILD) 2025 celebrations.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Himachal Pradesh joined Tripura, Mizoram, Goa, and Ladakh as the fifth fully literate state/UT in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The literacy milestone was celebrated on&lt;strong&gt; International Literacy Day 2025&lt;/strong&gt; with the&lt;strong&gt; theme &amp;quot;Promoting Literacy in the Digital Era&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;India&amp;#39;s literacy rate has increased from 74% in 2011 to 80.9% in 2023&amp;ndash;24, marking significant progress.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The ULLAS Nav Bharat Saaksharta Karyakram has been a major initiative for promoting literacy, enrolling over 3 crore learners.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;ULLAS Nav Bharat Saaksharta Karyakram&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A nationwide literacy program that has enrolled millions of learners and volunteers, providing learning in 26 Indian languages.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Digital Literacy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Digital literacy has become an essential part of the literacy movement in India, facilitating access to learning materials and skills development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Prime Minister&amp;rsquo;s Vision&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Prime Minister Narendra Modi emphasized education as the foundation of civilization and urged continuous efforts towards universal literacy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B - A - D - C.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

