&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India has improved its ranking to 38th place in the Global Innovation Index (GII) 2025, up from its 2020 position of 48th.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s ranking in the GII 2025 is 38th, showcasing its growing innovation performance globally.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India is ranked #1 among lower-middle-income economies and in the Central and Southern Asia region.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India has improved in specific sub-categories such as knowledge and technology outputs, where it ranks 22nd.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India continues to perform well in research, innovation ecosystems, and technology-driven growth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Top Countries: Switzerland,&amp;nbsp;Sweden,&amp;nbsp;United States of America.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Global Innovation Index (GII) 2025&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The GII assesses 139 countries using over 80 indicators, categorizing them into seven pillars to evaluate their innovation capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The index includes indicators like human capital, infrastructure, market sophistication, and knowledge outputs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Switzerland&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ranked #1 in the Global Innovation Index 2025 with a score of 66, leading global innovation performance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s Strengths and Weaknesses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengths: India ranks high in knowledge and technology outputs and human capital &amp;amp; research.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Weaknesses: India faces challenges in areas such as business sophistication, infrastructure, and institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public sector dominance in core industries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;150&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;India&amp;#39;s mixed economy model was characterized by a &lt;strong&gt;dominance of the public sector&lt;/strong&gt; in key and core industries such as steel, mining, power, transport, and communication. This was done to ensure strategic control and development in sectors crucial for national growth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;284&quot; data-start=&quot;152&quot;&gt;The public sector was given precedence in these industries to ensure equitable distribution of resources, regulate monopoly tendencies, and foster socio-economic development across regions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;400&quot; data-start=&quot;286&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Industrial Policy of 1948&lt;/strong&gt; and the subsequent &lt;strong&gt;Industrial Policy Resolution of 1956&lt;/strong&gt; explicitly laid out the framework for public sector dominance in industries that were considered vital to national interest. &lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;This makes Option 1 correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;550&quot; data-start=&quot;402&quot;&gt;Options 2, 3, and 4 are incorrect as they do not align with India&amp;#39;s mixed economy model. Licensing was introduced under the &lt;strong&gt;License Raj system&lt;/strong&gt;, privatization was limited, and the focus was not on consumerism but balanced economic development and industrialization.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;650&quot; data-start=&quot;552&quot;&gt;India&amp;#39;s mixed economy aimed to combine the advantages of both socialism and capitalism, ensuring state control in strategic sectors while allowing private enterprises to operate in non-strategic sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industrial Policy of 1948:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;750&quot; data-start=&quot;700&quot;&gt;This was the first industrial policy of independent India, highlighting the importance of public sector control in industries considered crucial for national security and development.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;850&quot; data-start=&quot;752&quot;&gt;It categorized industries into &lt;strong&gt;three groups&lt;/strong&gt;: industries exclusively managed by the state, industries that could be jointly managed by private and state entities, and industries left to private entrepreneurs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industrial Policy Resolution of 1956:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;950&quot; data-start=&quot;900&quot;&gt;This resolution further emphasized the dominance of the public sector in core industries such as iron and steel, heavy machinery, and atomic energy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1050&quot; data-start=&quot;952&quot;&gt;It aimed at achieving a &lt;strong&gt;socialist pattern of society&lt;/strong&gt; by promoting state ownership in key industries to reduce income inequalities and regional disparities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;License Raj System:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1150&quot; data-start=&quot;1100&quot;&gt;Under the License Raj system, introduced in the 1950s, the government strictly regulated private sector industries by requiring licenses for starting, expanding, and diversifying businesses.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1250&quot; data-start=&quot;1152&quot;&gt;This system was aimed at preventing monopolies, ensuring equitable distribution of resources, and promoting state control in strategic industries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Privatization:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1350&quot; data-start=&quot;1300&quot;&gt;While privatization was not a significant feature of India&amp;#39;s mixed economy during its early years, it gained momentum after the &lt;strong&gt;economic reforms of 1991&lt;/strong&gt;, which marked a shift towards liberalization.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1450&quot; data-start=&quot;1352&quot;&gt;In the mixed economy model, private sector participation was encouraged in non-core sectors to complement public sector efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Characteristics of India&amp;#39;s Mixed Economy:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1550&quot; data-start=&quot;1500&quot;&gt;The public sector was given a dominant role in strategic industries to ensure national security, equitable resource distribution, and socio-economic development.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1650&quot; data-start=&quot;1552&quot;&gt;The private sector was allowed to operate in non-strategic industries to foster entrepreneurship, innovation, and economic growth.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1750&quot; data-start=&quot;1652&quot;&gt;The government introduced various policies such as the &lt;strong&gt;Five-Year Plans&lt;/strong&gt; to guide economic development and balance public-private sector contributions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of Public Sector Dominance:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1850&quot; data-start=&quot;1800&quot;&gt;The establishment of &lt;strong&gt;BHEL (Bharat Heavy Electricals Limited)&lt;/strong&gt;, SAIL (Steel Authority of India Limited), and ONGC (Oil and Natural Gas Corporation) demonstrated public sector dominance in core industries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1950&quot; data-start=&quot;1852&quot;&gt;These industries were pivotal in achieving India&amp;#39;s goals of self-reliance and economic sovereignty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;17&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;284&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)&lt;/strong&gt; were adopted at the &lt;strong&gt;United Nations Sustainable Development Summit&lt;/strong&gt;, held in &lt;strong&gt;New York&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;September 2015&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;605&quot; data-start=&quot;482&quot;&gt;The SDGs are also referred to as the &lt;strong&gt;Global Goals&lt;/strong&gt;. They are a universal call to action to end poverty, protect the planet, and ensure that all people enjoy peace and prosperity by the year &lt;strong&gt;2030&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;692&quot; data-start=&quot;610&quot;&gt;There are a total of &lt;strong&gt;17 SDGs&lt;/strong&gt;, which address a wide range of global challenges, including &lt;strong&gt;poverty, inequality, climate change, environmental degradation, peace, and justice&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct option is 17.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1041&quot; data-start=&quot;850&quot;&gt;Each goal has specific &lt;strong&gt;targets&lt;/strong&gt; to be achieved, with a total of &lt;strong&gt;169 targets&lt;/strong&gt; across all the goals, making them comprehensive and interconnected in nature.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1162&quot; data-start=&quot;1046&quot;&gt;The SDGs succeeded the &lt;strong&gt;Millennium Development Goals (MDGs)&lt;/strong&gt;, which were in place from &lt;strong&gt;2000 to 2015&lt;/strong&gt;. The SDGs were designed to be more inclusive and detailed compared to the MDGs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1560&quot; data-start=&quot;1323&quot;&gt;The SDGs emphasize collaboration among governments, international organizations, and global stakeholders to achieve sustainable development worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1654&quot; data-start=&quot;1565&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;17 SDGs&lt;/strong&gt; include goals like &lt;strong&gt;No Poverty&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Zero Hunger&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Quality Education&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Gender Equality&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Climate Action&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Partnerships for the Goals&lt;/strong&gt;, among others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 17 Sustainable Development Goals:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2410&quot; data-start=&quot;2195&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 1:&lt;/strong&gt; No Poverty &amp;ndash; Focuses on ending poverty in all its forms everywhere.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2684&quot; data-start=&quot;2415&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 2:&lt;/strong&gt; Zero Hunger &amp;ndash; Aims to end hunger, achieve food security, improve nutrition, and promote sustainable agriculture.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3071&quot; data-start=&quot;2865&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 3:&lt;/strong&gt; Good Health and Well-being &amp;ndash; Ensures healthy lives and promotes well-being for all at all ages.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3250&quot; data-start=&quot;3076&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 4:&lt;/strong&gt; Quality Education &amp;ndash; Ensures inclusive and equitable quality education and promotes lifelong learning opportunities for all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3402&quot; data-start=&quot;3301&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 5:&lt;/strong&gt; Gender Equality &amp;ndash; Achieves gender equality and empowers all women and girls.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3580&quot; data-start=&quot;3407&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 6:&lt;/strong&gt; Clean Water and Sanitation &amp;ndash; Ensures availability and sustainable management of water and sanitation for all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3729&quot; data-start=&quot;3585&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 7:&lt;/strong&gt; Affordable and Clean Energy &amp;ndash; Ensures access to affordable, reliable, sustainable, and modern energy for all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 8:&lt;/strong&gt; Decent Work and Economic Growth &amp;ndash; Promotes sustained, inclusive, and sustainable economic growth, full and productive employment, and decent work for all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 9:&lt;/strong&gt; Industry, Innovation, and Infrastructure &amp;ndash; Builds resilient infrastructure, promotes inclusive and sustainable industrialization, and fosters innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 10:&lt;/strong&gt; Reduced Inequalities &amp;ndash; Reduces inequality within and among countries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 11:&lt;/strong&gt; Sustainable Cities and Communities &amp;ndash; Makes cities and human settlements inclusive, safe, resilient, and sustainable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 12:&lt;/strong&gt; Responsible Consumption and Production &amp;ndash; Ensures sustainable consumption and production patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 13:&lt;/strong&gt; Climate Action &amp;ndash; Takes urgent action to combat climate change and its impacts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 14:&lt;/strong&gt; Life Below Water &amp;ndash; Conserves and sustainably uses the oceans, seas, and marine resources.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 15:&lt;/strong&gt; Life on Land &amp;ndash; Protects, restores, and promotes sustainable use of terrestrial ecosystems, manages forests, combats desertification, and halts biodiversity loss.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 16:&lt;/strong&gt; Peace, Justice, and Strong Institutions &amp;ndash; Promotes peaceful and inclusive societies, provides access to justice for all, and builds effective, accountable institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal 17:&lt;/strong&gt; Partnerships for the Goals &amp;ndash; Strengthens the means of implementation and revitalizes the global partnership for sustainable development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of SDGs:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4636&quot; data-start=&quot;4411&quot;&gt;The SDGs are crucial for addressing the global challenges that include poverty, inequality, climate change, and environmental degradation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4761&quot; data-start=&quot;4641&quot;&gt;They are a part of the &lt;strong&gt;2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development&lt;/strong&gt;, which was adopted by all United Nations Member States in &lt;strong&gt;2015&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;5043&quot; data-start=&quot;4817&quot;&gt;The SDGs call for a collaborative approach where nations, private sectors, and civil society work together to achieve global sustainable development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Apr 12 2005&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;284&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The National Rural Health Mission (NRHM)&lt;/strong&gt; was launched by the &lt;strong&gt;Government of India&lt;/strong&gt; on &lt;strong&gt;April 12, 2005&lt;/strong&gt;. It aimed to provide accessible, affordable, and quality healthcare to the rural population, especially vulnerable groups.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;605&quot; data-start=&quot;482&quot;&gt;The mission was introduced as part of the &lt;strong&gt;National Health Policy&lt;/strong&gt; to address deficiencies in healthcare infrastructure and improve health indicators like &lt;strong&gt;infant mortality rate&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;maternal mortality rate&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;692&quot; data-start=&quot;610&quot;&gt;NRHM primarily targeted &lt;strong&gt;18 states&lt;/strong&gt; where health indicators were particularly poor. These included states like &lt;strong&gt;Bihar, Uttar Pradesh, Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt;, and others.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1041&quot; data-start=&quot;850&quot;&gt;The mission focused on strengthening the public health system through interventions like &lt;strong&gt;ASHA (Accredited Social Health Activist)&lt;/strong&gt;, improving infrastructure, and integrating primary, secondary, and tertiary healthcare services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1162&quot; data-start=&quot;1046&quot;&gt;NRHM also worked on improving &lt;strong&gt;sanitation, nutrition, and safe drinking water&lt;/strong&gt; as complementary health interventions. It sought to reduce gaps in healthcare access between urban and rural areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1560&quot; data-start=&quot;1323&quot;&gt;The mission emphasized &lt;strong&gt;community participation&lt;/strong&gt; and introduced mechanisms for decentralization to empower local health facilities and improve their functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1654&quot; data-start=&quot;1565&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Janani Suraksha Yojana&lt;/strong&gt;, a key component of NRHM, aimed to promote institutional deliveries and reduce maternal and infant mortality rates.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;2112&quot; data-start=&quot;2076&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Tue Apr 12 2005&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objectives of NRHM:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2410&quot; data-start=&quot;2195&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strengthening rural healthcare infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt; Building new health facilities like &lt;strong&gt;Primary Health Centres (PHCs)&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Community Health Centres (CHCs)&lt;/strong&gt;, and sub-centres.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2684&quot; data-start=&quot;2415&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Human resources:&lt;/strong&gt; Recruiting healthcare workers, including &lt;strong&gt;ASHA workers&lt;/strong&gt;, nurses, and doctors, to fill gaps in rural health services.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3071&quot; data-start=&quot;2865&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disease control:&lt;/strong&gt; Strengthening programs for communicable diseases like &lt;strong&gt;malaria, tuberculosis, and HIV/AIDS&lt;/strong&gt;, as well as non-communicable diseases.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Features:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3250&quot; data-start=&quot;3076&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ASHA workers:&lt;/strong&gt; Serving as a bridge between the healthcare system and the community, these workers provided essential health services and promoted awareness.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3729&quot; data-start=&quot;3585&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decentralization:&lt;/strong&gt; Empowering &lt;strong&gt;local governing bodies&lt;/strong&gt; like Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs) to plan and implement health initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3580&quot; data-start=&quot;3407&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Janani Suraksha Yojana:&lt;/strong&gt; Financial incentives for institutional deliveries to reduce maternal and infant mortality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Achievements:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3729&quot; data-start=&quot;3585&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Increased institutional deliveries:&lt;/strong&gt; A rise in institutional deliveries was observed across states due to programs like &lt;strong&gt;Janani Suraksha Yojana&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4636&quot; data-start=&quot;4411&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improved health indicators:&lt;/strong&gt; Significant improvements were seen in &lt;strong&gt;infant mortality rate&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;maternal mortality rate&lt;/strong&gt;, and life expectancy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NRHM&amp;#39;s integration:&lt;/strong&gt; In 2013, NRHM was subsumed under the &lt;strong&gt;National Health Mission (NHM)&lt;/strong&gt;, which also included the &lt;strong&gt;National Urban Health Mission (NUHM)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus Areas:&lt;/strong&gt; NRHM prioritized &lt;strong&gt;maternal health, child health, family planning, communicable diseases&lt;/strong&gt;, and infrastructure development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Funding Mechanism:&lt;/strong&gt; The mission received funding through a mix of &lt;strong&gt;central and state government contributions&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring shared responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;23 March.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 10px; &quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On this day, the&amp;nbsp;World Meteorological Organization (WMO) was established in the year 1950.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;WMO is headquartered&amp;nbsp;in &lt;strong&gt;Geneva, Switzerland.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The International Meteorological Organization (IMO), whose concept dates back &lt;strong&gt;to the Vienna International Meteorological Congress of 1873, &lt;/strong&gt;gave birth to the organisation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The theme for 2022 is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Early Warning and Early Action.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

